article.headline: Bradley 63, Missouri St. 57
article.story: SPRINGFIELD, Mo. -- Chris Roberts scored 14 second-half points to help Bradley University survive a Missouri State rally for a 63-57 win Saturday. Roberts, who finished with 22 points, scored a critical 3-pointer with 3:59 left to tie the game at 54 after Missouri State (7-7, 0-3 Missouri Valley) rallied from a 16-point first-half deficit to take the lead at 54-51 on two free throws by Wade Knapp with 6:02 left. Bradley (9-5, 3-0) held Missouri State to one field goal over the last 8:12, a 3-pointer by Kyle Weems with 1:58 that gave the Bears a 57-56 lead. Missouri State did not score again. Theron Wilson added 12 points for Bradley. Spencer Laurie and Will Creekmore each had 17 points for Missouri State.
